    "body": "I am using this `packages.yaml` file in `~/.spack/packages.yaml`:\r\n\r\n```\r\npackages:\r\n  all:\r\n    providers:\r\n      blas: [openblas]\r\n      lapack: [openblas]\r\n      mpi: [openmpi]\r\n  bison:\r\n    compiler: [clang@8.1.0-apple]\r\n  cmake:\r\n    compiler: [clang@8.1.0-apple]\r\n  gettext:\r\n    compiler: [clang@8.1.0-apple]\r\n  py_matplotlib:\r\n    compiler: [clang@8.1.0-apple]\r\n  pkg_config:\r\n    compiler: [clang@8.1.0-apple]\r\n  python:\r\n    compiler: [clang@8.1.0-apple]\r\n```\r\n\r\nYet when I install a package that depends on Python, and when this package is built with `gcc`, Spack wants to build Python with `gcc` as well. This is contrary to the documentation at `http://spack.readthedocs.io/en/latest/build_settings.html#concretization-preferences`.\r\n",
